    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "An escrow account is a neutral third-party account where funds and documents are held securely until the closing conditions are met. Your realtor is right to mention it, as it protects both the buyer and the seller by ensuring money isn't released until everything is in order. You can think of it as a safe deposit box managed by a lawyer or title company that only opens when the transaction is complete. Without this step, you'd be handing over your life savings directly to a seller, which is a major risk. It's a standard safety measure in real estate, especially in busy markets like Toronto.\n\nNow, do you have any questions about how the escrow process works or what documents you'll need to provide?",
