    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so basically someone else just holds the money so nobody gets cheated. is there a specific person or company that usually does this in ontario, or is it just like a random bank account?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, in Ontario, escrow is almost always handled by a specialized real estate lawyer or a specific type of title company, rather than just a random bank account. You can think of it as a \"legal escrow,\" where the lawyer acts as the neutral third party to ensure the deal is legally sound before money changes hands. While some banks offer escrow services, they are less common for residential real estate than the specialized law firms you'll typically see in the Toronto market. It's a crucial step because the lawyer verifies all the paperwork, checks for liens, and ensures the title is clear before they release the funds.\n\nWould you like to know what to look for when choosing a lawyer for your closing?",
